snippet: Amid intense opposition to its plan for a liquid-propane storage tank in Searsport, Me., DCP Midstream Partners abruptly pulled its application.
abstract: Denver oil company DCP Midstream Partners abruptly withdraws application to build 14-story liquid-propane storage tank on Maine coast, bringing sudden halt to contentious battle that has raged for years in tiny town of Searsport.
lead_paragraph: Amid intense opposition to its plan for a liquid-propane storage tank in Searsport, Me., DCP Midstream Partners abruptly pulled its application.

headline.seo: DCP Midstream Partners Withdraws Plan for Maine Town
headline.main: Denver Oil Concern Withdraws Its Plan for Big Tank in Maine
headline.print_headline: Denver Oil Concern Withdraws Its Plan for Big Tank in Maine
